1. Scholarships or financial aid can make school accessible without wealthy parents.
2. Government-funded education programs may provide free or affordable schooling.
3. Community support or sponsorships can help cover educational costs.
4. Part-time work or student loans can enable students to afford school independently.
5. Some schools offer sliding scale tuition based on family income.
6. Online or alternative education options may be more affordable.
7. Wealthy parents are not the only means to access education; other resources exist.